FOOT & MOUTH DISEASE - MAGHREB (14): MOROCCO (CASABLANCA-SETTAT), SEROTYPE O, BOVINE, SPREAD
********************************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

In this update:
[1] El Jadida: 2nd outbreak, bovine
[2] Q&A: official's update

******
[1] El Jadida: 2nd outbreak, bovine
Date: Mon 9 Nov 2015
Source: Alyaoum24 [in Arabic, trans. Mod.AB, edited]
http://www.alyaoum24.com/418036.html


The Regional Director of the National Health Security Office of foodstuffs (ONSSA) for Casablanca-Settat, Abdallah Ossoual, declared on [Sun 8 Nov 2015] that at least one case of foot-and-mouth disease [FMD] was diagnosed in a cattle herd in Saed hamlet, Al Haouzia district, in El Jadida province. This finding was confirmed through laboratory testing carried out on [Sat 7 Nov 2015] within the ongoing FMD surveillance program.

Ossoual added that his directorate, together with the local authorities and the Department of Agriculture of the Ministry of Agriculture and Fisheries, proceeded on [Mon 9 Nov 2015] morning with the destruction of the infected cow in addition to the in-contact animals, including 3 cows and 8 calves, to prevent the spread of the disease among livestock, as legally required.

ONSSA issued a report last week [week of 2 Nov 2015] confirming the emergence of FMD virus in Morocco and stressing that local veterinary services should activate the recommended control measures to curb the spread of this disease to other provinces. Among these measures is a ban on bringing affected farm animals as well as products of animal origin (milk and meat) into or out of the affected area and the on-site [destruction] of all infected or suspected-to-be-infected animals.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-MENA
